events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Heisman Trophy hopeful Deshaun Watson threw for 289 yards and three touchdowns and ran for 2 TDs, and No. 1 Clemson captured the ACC championship by holding off North Carolina.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemson bests UNC for ACC title, likely CFP spot

events.name: Florida Gators at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Heisman Trophy favorite Derrick Henry rushed for 189 bruising yards and No. 2 Alabama all but locked up its spot in the College Football Playoff, beating No. 18 Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henry breaks Herschel's mark in Bama triumph

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: L.J. Scott lunged across the goal line with 27 seconds left to push Michigan State past unbeaten Iowa, giving the Spartans a Big Ten title and likely spot in the College Football Playoff.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late TD gives No. 5 Michigan St. Big Ten crown

notes.headline: Pac-12 Championship Game presented by Dr Pepper

headlines.description: Christian McCaffrey broke Barry Sanders' 27-year-old all-purpose yardage record to lead No. 7 Stanford to a Pac-12 title with a 41-22 win over No. 20 USC.

video.headline: McCaffrey, Stanford roll to Pac-12 Title

headlines.shortLinkText: McCaffrey feat highlights Stanford's Pac-12 title

headlines.description: Tyrone Swoopes threw for 151 yards with a touchdown in his first Texas start since the opener, and the Longhorns held on for a 23-17 victory that knocked Baylor out of Sugar Bowl contention.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor out of Sugar Bowl after loss to Texas

headlines.description: Greg Ward Jr. ran for 148 yards and two touchdowns as Houston got a 24-13 win over Temple in the inaugural American Athletic Conference championship game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ward leads Houston to American title

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers

headlines.description: Brandon Doughty threw for 410 yards with three touchdown passes and Western Kentucky came from behind to defeat Southern Mississippi 45-28 in the Conference USA Championship Game on Saturday.

video.headline: Western Kentucky rallies to win Conference USA title

headlines.shortLinkText: Western Kentucky beats Southern Miss 45-28 for CUSA title

events.name: Colgate Raiders at James Madison Dukes

notes.headline: NCAA DIVISION I FOOTBALL CHAMPIONSHIP - SECOND ROUND

headlines.description: Jake Melville threw two touchdown passes and ran for two more, leading Colgate to a 44-38 upset win over James Madison on Saturday in the second round of the FCS playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Melville leads Colgate to 44-38 win over James Madison

events.name: Georgia State Panthers at Georgia Southern Eagles

headlines.description: Nick Arbuckle threw for 346 yards and three touchdowns and Georgia State defeated rival Georgia Southern 34-7 on Saturday to become bowl eligible for the first time in school history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia State smacks rival Georgia Southern, 34-7

events.name: Texas State Bobcats at Arkansas State Red Wolves

headlines.description: Fredi Knighten threw two touchdown passes and ran in another Saturday to lead Arkansas State to the Sun Belt Conference title with a 55-17 win over Texas State.

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Louisiana Monroe Warhawks

headlines.description: Trey Caldwell's fourth-quarter interception return for a touchdown proved the difference and Louisiana-Monroe beat New Mexico State 42-35 in a game filled with big plays.

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Wide receiver Cody Cook led Kansas State to a pair of touchdowns as the emergency quarterback, Morgan Burns returned a kickoff 97 yards for the go-ahead score and the Wildcats beat West Virginia
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas State rallies for 24-23 win over West Virginia

events.name: Troy Trojans at Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns

headlines.description: Brandon Silvers threw for 320 yards and four touchdowns to lead Troy to a 41-17 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Troy coasts to 41-17 win over Louisiana-Lafayette

events.name: Appalachian State Mountaineers at South Alabama Jaguars

headlines.description: Jalin Moore ran for two touchdowns, including the go-ahead score with 1:16 left and Appalachian State beat South Alabama 34-27 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Appalachian State wins 10th game, beats South Alabama 34-27

events.name: Air Force Falcons at San Diego State Aztecs

notes.headline: Sports Authority Mountain West Championship Game

headlines.description: Donny Hageman kicked a 46-yard field goal with 5:10 to go and San Diego State beat Air Force 27-24 to win the Mountain West Conference championship, the Aztecs' first outright title since 1986.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hageman's 46-yard field goal lifts SDSU to MWC title
